==========================================================================================
KEY FINDINGS
==========================================================================================

1. LARGEST SINGLE GAIN: Phase 4a (FL-guided cache replacement) delivers +2.03pp on average.
   Fixing the random eviction bug alone outperforms the original system across all CS.

2. PHASE 4b CONTRIBUTION: Staleness-aware FL aggregation adds +0.18pp on average.
   Effect is stronger at large cache sizes (CS>=300: +0.76–1.27pp) where the FL model
   quality matters more. Slight negative at CS=50 is within run-to-run variance.

3. PHASE 4c CONTRIBUTION: MARL cooperative caching adds +0.31pp on average.
   Largest gain at CS=400 (+0.92pp) — the high-dim state where a single agent struggles
   most. MARL's cooperative cache diversification is most valuable at large cache sizes.

4. CUMULATIVE SYSTEM: Full CAFR system (+4a+4b+4c) achieves:
   - +2.52pp average cache hit rate improvement vs baseline
   - -2.47ms average request delay reduction vs baseline
   - MCAF beats ε-Greedy at EVERY cache size (50–400)

5. DELAY MONOTONICALLY IMPROVES: Each phase adds measurable delay reduction
   4a: -0.34ms avg | 4b: -1.09ms avg | 4c: -1.04ms avg → total -2.47ms avg

